Alembic migrations for the Fibre Mold Plant backend.

The database URL is read from app settings (app.core.config.settings.database_url)
in env.py — do NOT put a URL in alembic.ini.

Common commands (run from the backend/ directory, or pass -c <path>/alembic.ini):

  alembic upgrade head            # apply all pending migrations
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
  alembic current                 # show the DB's current revision
  alembic history                 # list revisions
  alembic stamp head              # mark DB as at head WITHOUT running migrations

At container start, entrypoint.sh runs an adopt-or-upgrade sequence:
if a legacy pre-Alembic DB is detected (users table exists, alembic_version
does not) it stamps the baseline, then always runs `alembic upgrade head`.

To create a new schema change: edit the models, then autogenerate a revision
and review it before committing.
